# Deployment and testing rules (production)

This host runs **production only**. There is no local development realm—treat every deploy as production-facing. Use backups, maintenance windows, and off-host validation when you need isolated experimentation.

## MCP (operations)

- **Notion**: Before assuming service names, log directories (e.g. under `/data/logs` vs `env/dist/logs`), or restart procedures, use **`notion-search`** / **`notion-fetch`** (see `.cursor/rules/mcp-usage.mdc`, `.cursor/reference/mcp-tools-inventory.md`).
- **azerothcore**: **`soap_check_connection`**, **`soap_server_info`** after restarts; **`soap_reload_table`** / **`soap_execute_command`** only when policy allows and SOAP is not exposed to untrusted networks.
- **oldmanwarcraft-api-remote**: **`omw_get_server_status`**, **`omw_health_check`**, **`omw_get_server_population`** for site/API view of live state—**not** a substitute for SSH/systemd runbooks; use with user approval for write/API-heavy tools.
- **fetch** / **firecrawl** / **exa** / **deepwiki**: External docs and troubleshooting; cross-check with Notion + repo.

## Pre-deployment checklist

<pre_deployment>
- Code compiles without errors and warnings (or known-acceptable warnings documented)
- Database backups taken and verified (world, characters, playerbots as applicable)
- SQL reviewed for shared `acore_world` impact and rollback path
- SmartAI / proc / condition changes sanity-checked (queries, phase masks, links)
- Maintenance window or player impact considered for restarts and long migrations
- Documentation or Notion runbook updated if operational steps change
</pre_deployment>

## Backup procedures

<backup_rules>
- Backup world: `mysqldump -uacore -pacore acore_world > backup_world_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).sql`
- Backup characters: `mysqldump -uacore -pacore acore_characters > backup_characters_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).sql`
- Backup playerbots: `mysqldump -uacore -pacore acore_playerbots > backup_playerbots_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).sql`
- Compress: `gzip backup_*.sql`
- Verify: `ls -lh backup_*.sql`
- Store copies off the hot path; test restore periodically
</backup_rules>

## Database updates

<database_update>
- Schedule writes during agreed low-impact windows when possible
- Stop worldserver (or use your approved online migration process): e.g. `service ac-worldserver stop`
- Verify stopped: `systemctl status ac-worldserver`
- Apply: `mysql -uacore -pacore acore_world < update.sql`
- Verify: `mysql -uacore -pacore acore_world -e "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM <table>"`
- Check CLI output for errors
- Start server and confirm clean startup logs
</database_update>

## Code deployment

<code_deployment>
- Rebuild when C++ changed: `cd build && cmake .. && make -j$(nproc)` (adjust paths to your tree)
- Install/restart per your layout (`make install`, rsync, container rebuild, etc.)
- Ensure module list and configs match what production expects
</code_deployment>

## Configuration updates

<config_update>
- Compare dist to live: e.g. `cp conf/dist/modules/<module>.conf.dist env/dist/etc/modules/<module>.conf` then merge edits
- Validate non-comment lines have sensible values
- Restart or reload per module requirements; watch startup logs
</config_update>

## Server startup

<startup_rules>
- Start: `service ac-worldserver start` (or docker compose / your unit)
- Monitor: `systemctl status ac-worldserver`
- Logs: often `env/dist/logs/Server.log` or a mounted path such as `/data/logs/Server.log`—use the path your deployment actually uses
- Confirm modules loaded; spot-check one critical feature
</startup_rules>

## Verification

<verification_rules>
- `grep -iE "error|critical|fatal"` on recent log files
- Confirm expected “loaded” lines for custom modules
- In-game or GM checks for the changed behavior
- Watch for player reports and metric spikes after deploy
</verification_rules>

## Rollback procedure

<rollback_rules>
- Stop server
- Restore DB from known-good dump if data migration was involved
- Revert Git / redeploy previous artifact: `git revert <commit>` or redeploy last image
- Rebuild/restart
- Monitor logs; document cause and follow-up
</rollback_rules>

## Optional staging elsewhere

If you maintain a **separate** dev/staging host or container stack (not on this machine), run experimental SQL, ASan builds, and destructive tests **there** first. This rule file does not assume that stack exists.

## Post-deployment monitoring

<monitoring_rules>
- Daily: service health, error log tail, disk space
- Weekly: broader log review, backup success, obvious DB bloat
- Monthly: dependency/upstream merge planning, security patches, module compatibility after upstream pulls
</monitoring_rules>

## Useful commands

<useful_commands>
- Status: `systemctl status ac-worldserver`
- Logs: `tail -f env/dist/logs/Server.log` or `tail -f /data/logs/Server.log` as appropriate
- Backup: `mysqldump -uacore -pacore acore_world > backup.sql`
- Restore: `mysql -uacore -pacore acore_world < backup.sql`
- In-game reloads when supported: `.reload smart_scripts`, `.reload spell_proc`, `.reload conditions`
</useful_commands>
